# Cursor Rules for Ausna Project

## Style Guide Reference
ALWAYS refer to `STYLE_GUIDE.md` for design system guidelines including:
- Typography (fonts, sizes, weights)
- Colors (primary, secondary, semantic colors)
- Buttons (variants, sizes, states)
- Cards (padding, shadows, borders)
- Forms (inputs, labels, validation states)
- Spacing and layout patterns

## Design System Principles
1. **Consistency**: Use predefined design tokens from `STYLE_GUIDE.md` and `tailwind.config.js`
2. **Accessibility**: Ensure proper contrast ratios and semantic HTML
3. **Responsive**: Mobile-first approach with Tailwind breakpoints
4. **Component Reuse**: Prefer existing components from `components/` directory

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes (avoid custom CSS when possible)
- Follow existing component patterns in `components/` directory
- Use 'use client' directive only when necessary (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)

## When Creating New Components
1. Check `STYLE_GUIDE.md` for design patterns
2. Use design tokens from `tailwind.config.js`
3. Follow existing component structure patterns
4. Ensure responsive design (mobile-first)
5. Include proper TypeScript types

## When Styling Elements
- **Buttons**: ALWAYS use the `Button` component from `@/components/ui` instead of inline button styles. Use variants: primary, secondary, success, danger, text
- **Cards**: ALWAYS use the `Card` component from `@/components/ui` instead of inline card styles. Use variants: default, compact, spacious, subtle
- **Typography**: ALWAYS use `Title`, `Subtitle`, `Content`, or `UIText` components from `@/components/ui` instead of inline text styles. NEVER use direct text size/weight classes like `text-lg`, `font-bold`, etc.
  - `Title`: For headings and titles (large, regular, black)
  - `Subtitle`: For subtitles (extra large, regular, black)
  - `Content`: For body content (same size as title, gray)
  - `UIText`: For UI elements like labels, captions (smaller size)
- **Forms**: Use form input/label patterns from STYLE_GUIDE.md
- **Colors**: Use semantic color tokens (primary, secondary, success, danger, etc.)

## Component Usage
- **IMPORTANT**: Always import and use `Button`, `Card`, `Title`, `Subtitle`, `Content`, and `UIText` from `@/components/ui` instead of creating inline styled elements
- This ensures style changes propagate automatically across the entire application
- Example: `import { Button, Card, Title, Subtitle, Content, UIText } from '@/components/ui'`
- **Typography Rules**: 
  - NEVER use `text-*` or `font-*` classes directly
  - ALWAYS use `Title`, `Subtitle`, `Content`, or `UIText` components
  - Only 4 font types allowed: title, subtitle, content, ui

## Layout Structure
- Follow the root layout structure defined in STYLE_GUIDE.md
- Max content width: 800px (via CSS variable `--max-content-width`)
- Background: `bg-gray-50`
- Pages render content directly without wrapper divs

